properties.media:imagetext:
HOW TO GET A FLYING START
BEFORE YOU LEAVE THE GROUND
Let the PSA Automatic
Check-in Machine transport
you past check-in lines.
The Automatic Check-in
Machine from PSA. It's the time-
saving innovation that lets you
forget about long check-in lines
at the airport. Because once
you've made your PSA reserva-
tion, the Automatic Check-in
Machine lets you get your
boarding pass and seat assign-
ment in seconds (up to 2 hours
prior to your time of departure).
You can even purchase your
ticket right then and there if you
haven't already done so at your
travel agent. It's fast, easy and
hassle-free.
To use the Automatic
Check-in Machine, make a
reservation first.
(If you haven't made reserva-
tions before arrival at the airport,
use the red PSA reservation
phone next to the machine.)
* Make your flight reservations
in the name as it appears on
your major credit card when
speaking to the reservations
agent.
• If you're a PSA Executive Flyer,
be sure to give the reservations
agent your Executive Flyer
number. This will assure your
preferred seat assignment.
It's easy to use the
PSA Automatic Check-in
Machine.
Insert Your Credit Card.
• Most major credit cards
(or your PSA credit card)
will activate the machine.
Your card is used only to
locate your reservation. Your
flight is not billed to your credit
card unless you are purchasing
your ticket through the Auto-
matic Check-in Machine.
• Since the card is only drawn
part way into the machine, there
is no chance of losing your card
as with some card-activated
machines.
2 Mote
Make Your Selections.
machine
will display
easy-to-follow
Instructions
on the screen.
• Enter seat
preference
(window or
aisle, smoking
or non-
smoking).
•PSA Executive Flyers will
automatically receive their
preferred seat assignment.
• The
machine
will print
your board-
ing pass
and/or ticket. Executive Flyers
should put their personalized
PSA stickers
on the ticket
to insure
mileage credit.
• If you don't
have a con-
firmed reserva-
fion, you can
still purchase a
standby ticket
through the Au-
tomatic Check-
in Machine.
You can then get your seat
assignment at the gate from.
your PSA ticket agent.
RESERVATION
You're On Your Way.
• Remove your boarding
pass. Staple it to your ticket,
using the stapler provided. (If
you are purchasing a ticket
directly through the Automatic
Check-in Machine, the ticket
itself is your boarding pass.)
RESENEATION
TICKENO-BY
• Present the boarding pass
to the flight attendant. You will
retain the portion labelled
boarding pass/receipt.
• For connecting flights, use the
Automatic Check-in Machine at
your connecting airport or see a
PSA ticket agent.
PSA
REBE PRESS
